 NATIONAL Publicity Secretary, Arewa Consultative Forum, Emmanuel Yawe, is dead. Mr Yawe, a distinguished journalist and author, is reported to have died in his sleep on March 10th, 2022. He was, at various times, Member, Editorial Board of Advisers, The Point Newspaper; Editorial Board Member, People’s Daily Newspaper; Managing Editor, New Sentinel Newspaper; and Editor, Crystal International News Magazine. The renowned journalist was also Managing Director of Gongola Press Limited between 1988 and 1992; Director-General, Governor’s Office, Gongola State (1987 – 1988); and Editor, Sunday Triumph Newspapers (1984 – 1987). He was also Chief Press Secretary, Governor’s Office, Gongola State (1983 – 1983); and Editorial Board Member, New Nigerian Newspaper (1982 – 1983). A graduate of Political Science from the University of Ibadan in 1979, Emmanuel YAWE was born in Donga local government area of Taraba state on 21st October, 1956. Burial arrangements will be announced in due course by the deceased’s family. 